			"lessonTitle": "Introduction",
			"lessonText": ["Connecting characters are those, which can connect to both sides.", "Let's look at the letter meem <span class='ar-text'>م</span>. It has different forms:"],
			"lessonNotes": ["<span class='ar-text'>م</span> - not connecting to other characters. This is called the independent form.", "<span class='ar-text'>مـ</span> - connecting to the next character. This is called the initial form.", "<span class='ar-text'>ـمـ</span> - connecting on both sides. This is called the middle form.", "<span class='ar-text'>ـم</span> - connecting to the previous character. This is called the final form."]
		},
		{
			"lessonTitle": "Watch out!",
			"lessonText": ["Initial form does not mean that it can only occur at the beginning of a word. Look at: <br><span class='ar-text'>رمد</span>", "After a non-connecting character the initial form is used."],
			"lessonNotes": ["Similarly, the independent form can occur at the end of a word. For example: <br><span class='ar-text'>مدم</span>", "Time for some practice!"]
		}
